We’re celebrating #WorldCocktailDay with a MIN8® by @sonjijam of Palermo’s @13_bootleg. Featured in @50bestbars #PassTheShaker series, this highball twist provides the perfect refreshment for a spring evening.

MIN8®
50 ml Michter's US*1 Bourbon
15 ml Mancino Red Vermouth
1 dash bitters
Chinotto
Build in the glass (highball). Fill with chinotto. Stir. Garnish with orange zest.

#WorldCocktailDay #PassTheShaker #Worlds50BestBars #50BestBars #MakeItMichters #Michters #MichtersWhiskey

node.text: Our cooperage prepares our barrels to Michter’s specifications of toasting and charring. When toasting a barrel, the interior of the barrel heats for a specified period of time at a specified temperature. As the oak is heated during toasting, compounds in the wood break down in a way that will lead to the release of desirable aroma, flavor and color during the eventual aging of the whiskey. Once toasting is complete, the barrel is charred to Michter’s specifications. This process is done to further create flavor, color, and aroma through caramelization of sugars. You can see with our toasted and charred barrel, how deep the whiskey seeps into the wood extracting rich flavor, color and aroma vs. the alternative of just charring the barrel. Just another added step to our Michter’s smooth, rich and flavorful house style.

node.text:
We're on a mission to prove that Michter's makes everything taste better. For example, Salted Maple Pecan Monkey Bread which is made with our US*1 Bourbon.

Salted Maple Pecan Monkey Bread 
8 Servings 

Ingredients 
2 tbsp Michter’s US*1 Bourbon
1 cup pecans, roughly chopped 
1/4 cup heavy cream
1/4 cup maple syrup
1/4 cup brown sugar 
6 tbsp salted butter
1 tsp vanilla extract
1tsp salt
1 16oz Ready to Bake Biscuit Dough
1 tbsp sugar 2 tsp cinnamon powder
Sea salt flakes (optional) 

Instructions 
1. Preheat oven to 350F. 2. Line a loaf pan with parchment paper and spread the chopped pecans evenly. 3. In sauce pot, combine heavy cream, maple syrup, brown sugar and butter. 4. Heat until the butter and sugar is melted and simmering.
5. Turn off heat and add in vanilla & Michter’s US*1 Bourbon. 6. Pour the sauce onto the prepared loaf pan.
7. Separate the Biscuit dough and put them in a zip lock bag with sugar and cinnamon. Seal and shake until the dough pieces are evenly coated. 
8. Place the biscuit dough in the prepared loaf pan.
9. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. 
10. Sprinkle with sea salt flakes.
11. Enjoy with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
